Text: KERRY: Well, first of all, Bob, thank you for moderating tonight.
Speech: Well, first of all, Bob, thank you for moderating tonight.

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: Thank you, Arizona State, for welcoming us.
Speech: Thank you, Arizona State, for welcoming us.
Speaker: KERRY
Name: John F. Kerry

Text: And thank you to the Presidential Commission for undertaking this enormous task.
Speech: And thank you to the Presidential Commission for undertaking this enormous task.

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: We're proud to be here.
Speech: We're proud to be here.
Speaker: KERRY
Name: John F. Kerry

Text: Mr. President, I'm glad to be here with you again to share similarities and differences with the American people.
Speech: Mr. President, I'm glad to be here with you again to share similarities and differences with the American people.

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: Will we ever be safe and secure again?
Speech: Will we ever be safe and secure again?

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: We absolutely must be.
Speech: We absolutely must be.
Speaker: KERRY
Name: John F. Kerry

Text: That's the goal.
Speech: That's the goal.

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: Now, how do we achieve it is the most critical component of it.
Speech: Now, how do we achieve it is the most critical component of it.

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: I believe that this president, regrettably, rushed us into a war, made decisions about foreign policy, pushed alliances away.
Speech: I believe that this president, regrettably, rushed us into a war, made decisions about foreign policy, pushed alliances away.

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: And, as a result, America is now bearing this extraordinary burden where we are not as safe as we ought to be.

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: The measurement is not: Are we safer?
Speech: The measurement is not: Are we safer?

Text: The measurement is: Are we as safe as we ought to be?
Speech: Are we as safe as we ought to be?

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: And there are a host of options that this president had available to him, like making sure that at all our ports in America containers are inspected.

Name: John F. Kerry

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: So we can do a better job of homeland security.

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: I can do a better job of waging a smarter, more effective war on terror and guarantee that we will go after the terrorists.
Speech: I can do a better job of waging a smarter, more effective war on terror and guarantee that we will go after the terrorists.
Speaker: KERRY
Name: John F. Kerry

Text: I will hunt them down, and we'll kill them, we'll capture them.
Speech: I will hunt them down, and we'll kill them, we'll capture them.

Name: John F. Kerry

Text: We'll do whatever is necessary to be safe.
Speech: We'll do whatever is necessary to be safe.
Speaker: KERRY
Name: John F. Kerry

Text: But I pledge this to you, America: I will do it in the way that Franklin Roosevelt and Ronald Reagan and John Kennedy and others did, where we build the strongest alliances, where the world joins together, where we have the best intelligence and where we are able, ultimately, to be more safe and secure.
Speech: But I pledge this to you, America: I will do it in the way that Franklin Roosevelt and Ronald Reagan and John Kennedy and others did, where we build the strongest alliances, where the world joins together, where we have the best intelligence and where we are able, ultimately, to be more safe and secure.

Name: John F. Kerry

Speech: Bob, thank you very much.

Name: George W. Bush

Speech: I want to thank Arizona State as well.

Name: George W. Bush

Text: Yes, we can be safe and secure, if we stay on the offense against the terrorists and if we spread freedom and liberty around the world.

Name: George W. Bush
